<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 1:01PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF HAMPTON, COLLETON AND
ALLENDALE COUNTIES...
At 100 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm over Miley, or near Hampton, moving northeast at
35 mph.
HAZARD...strong winds 45 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar Indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Some locations in the path of this storm include...
Colleton, Smoaks, Lodge, Williams, Crocketville, Ruffin, Padgetts and
Miley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>Report damage directly to the Charleston National Weather Service at
888-383-2024 when it is safe to do so. You can also email your
report to nws.charlestonsc@noaa.gov.</instruction>
